description:
In this episode, we learn about the life of Anna Knight. She was an Adventist pioneer in every sense of the word. From the remarkable story of her conversion and acceptance of the Sabbath, her education and missionary service in India, and the pioneering work in education, particularly amongst the African American community - she was a trail blazer who impacted not just her generation, but also those who would come after her.

To find out more about Anna Knight visit our website to read our extended article.
